dialog.text: Where are we, this doesn't look like Fred's house?
I'm not sure. I just let the Christmas magic fly us.
Say, that does look like Fred and his wife Clara.
Hmm. Humid weather, bamboo and pineapples everywhere. I think we're in Hawaii. Perhaps they took a vacation.
They had Christmas in Hawaii without me?!
I'm glad I cut them out of my will.
I don't think they can see us. Let’s go listen to what they are saying.
Ha ha hah. And then my Uncle Scrooge said Christmas was a humbug.
Oh, dear me. And he was beside himself with all the talk of figgy pudding. Ha hah hah.
Oh dear, and then what did he do?
Slammed the door in my face. Poor old coot! He'd prefer to spend Christmas alone than a sunny trip to Hawaii. I pity him, I do.
Oh Fred. I bet if you told Scrooge about the trip he would have come.
It's a good thing he didn't. Such a Debbie Downer, he is.
Well, let's toast to Scrooge, the crustiest old geezer of them all.
To Scrooge!
Hmm. something smells like chicken. Do you smell it?
I agree. It’s quite un-pheasant. ha ha ha!
I'm thinking of an animal. It goes oink oink oink. What is it?
Scrooge when he wallows in his money. Ha ha ha!
Oh how droll!
There's no time for coffee right now. Get back to some heart melting action.
